 A newly declassified United States Department of Defense video is reigniting worldwide fascination with UFOs after the Pentagon released infrared footage of a mysterious “eight-pointed star” object moving across the sky. Captured by U.S. military personnel in the Middle East in 2013, the strange object appears to float, pulse, and leave behind a glowing thermal trail before suddenly vanishing from the sensor’s field of view. Officials included the footage in the latest release of classified UAP — Unidentified Anomalous Phenomena — files as part of a broader transparency initiative ordered by President Donald Trump. The bizarre shape and unexplained movement have triggered intense debate online, with UFO enthusiasts calling it groundbreaking while skeptics suggest infrared distortion or sensor anomalies. As more Pentagon files emerge, questions continue to grow over what exactly U.S. military systems have been tracking in restricted airspace for decades.
